Class Input

  • java.lang.Object
    • Input

  • public class Input
extends java.lang.Object
    The Input class extends the standard input the java to get precise data and correct formats.
    See Also:
    BufferedReader, InputStreamReader, IOException

      • readIntInRange

        public int readIntInRange(int start,
                          int end)
        Reads an integer value in a range from A (start) to B (end).

        Important: This method implements the readInt method of the class for its operation.

        Parameters:
        start - The start integer - A
        end - The end integer - B
        Returns:
        an integer value in the specified range.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the established range is invalid.

        For example:

                   readIntInRange(3, 2)

        Where the start parameter is greater than the end parameter.

        See Also:
        readInt()
